    <text>
        <body>
            <head>59. Personal Note Prepared by the Deputy Secretary of State (<persName
                    corresp="recrWcRZxYT57GiP4">Dam</persName>)<note n="1" place="foot"
                    type="source" xml:id="d59fn1">Source: Department of State, Executive
                    Secretariat, <gloss target="#t_SSI_1">S/S-I</gloss> Records: Deputy Secretary
                        <persName corresp="recrWcRZxYT57GiP4">Dam</persName>’s Official Files, Lot
                    85D308, Personal Notes of Deputy Secretary—<persName corresp="recrWcRZxYT57GiP4"
                        >Kenneth W. Dam</persName>—Oct. 1982–Sept. 1983. Secret. Dictated on April
                    14.</note>
            </head>
            <opener>
                <dateline rendition="#right">
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1983-04-14"
                        >April 14, 1983</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p>[Omitted here are discussions not related to <gloss target="#t_START_1"><rs
                        corresp="recGzN4S83GSdMO7O" type="event">START</rs></gloss>.]</p>
            <p>After a quick attendance at a Situation Room meeting chaired by Judge <persName
                    corresp="rec5nWAotd8wedNxI">Clark</persName> on public diplomacy, I attended a
                lengthy meeting that <persName corresp="rece7NCQ7Hh9DICyN">the Secretary</persName>
                had with Ambassador <persName corresp="rec62rNu2glRunbNq">Dobrynin</persName>.<note
                    n="2" place="foot" xml:id="d59fn2">The memorandum of conversation is scheduled
                    for publication in <ref target="frus1981-88v04#d42">
                        <hi rendition="simple_italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1981–1988, vol. IV,
                        Soviet Union, January 1983—March 1985, Document 42</ref>.</note> This was a
                meeting devoted to probing whether there was a possibility for making some progress
                in the <gloss target="#t_START_1"><rs corresp="recGzN4S83GSdMO7O" type="event"
                        >START</rs></gloss> negotiations. Ambassador <persName
                    corresp="recCAUUmNdxvAWExm">Rowny</persName> was present. <pb facs="0246"
                    n="217" xml:id="pg_217"/> (Incidentally, <persName corresp="recJYLsVHtwd9Q6nh"
                    >Kenneth Adelman</persName> was confirmed by the Senate 57 to 42 just before the
                    <persName corresp="rec62rNu2glRunbNq">Dobrynin</persName> meeting began.)</p>
            <p>Secretary <persName corresp="rece7NCQ7Hh9DICyN">Shultz</persName> asked <persName
                    corresp="rec62rNu2glRunbNq">Dobrynin</persName> three questions. One had to do
                with whether or not some compromise was possible between the Soviet number of 1800
                    <rs corresp="recMGkwDnbHpEWvfN" type="topic">strategic delivery vehicles</rs>
                and our number of 850 missiles and 400 bombers. The second question had to do with
                whether the Soviets were prepared to back off of their position that there could be
                no <gloss target="#t_ALCM_1"><rs corresp="rec3r8I0hO6jAW3Fm" type="topic"
                    >ALCMs</rs></gloss>; <persName corresp="rece7NCQ7Hh9DICyN">the
                    Secretary</persName> referred to this as the Soviet zero option. The third
                question had to do with how the Soviets were prepared to meet our security concern
                raised by their heavy and medium-weight missiles. This is an attempt to put some
                life in the <gloss target="#t_START_1"><rs corresp="recGzN4S83GSdMO7O" type="event"
                        >START</rs></gloss> talks. <persName corresp="rec62rNu2glRunbNq"
                    >Dobrynin</persName> agreed to get back to us with an answer from his
                government.</p>
            <p>[Omitted here are discussions not related to <gloss target="#t_START_1"><rs
                        corresp="recGzN4S83GSdMO7O" type="event">START</rs></gloss>.]</p>
        </body>
